post_text:
Each year, the KC Royals honor our students who achieved perfect attendance throughout the entire school year by sending them Royals tickets to enjoy a game over the Summer. However, with the unusual end to the school year and the changes made to professional baseball, the Royals had to adapt as well.

This year, the KC Royals honored our students with perfect attendance by showcasing their name on their Jumbotron in the stadium and snapped these photos to help us recognize them.

We would like to congratulate these students again for their perfect attendance achievement during the 2019-2020 school year! Way to go!
text:
Each year, the KC Royals honor our students who achieved perfect attendance throughout the entire school year by sending them Royals tickets to enjoy a game over the Summer. However, with the unusual end to the school year and the changes made to professional baseball, the Royals had to adapt as well.

This year, the KC Royals honored our students with perfect attendance by showcasing their name on their Jumbotron in the stadium and snapped these photos to help us recognize them.

We would like to congratulate these students again for their perfect attendance achievement during the 2019-2020 school year! Way to go!

post_text:
Hello family, friends, colleagues, Leeton students and staff,

Two days ago I was notified by David Luther from MOSPRA that I received the Missouri School Public Relations Association, Administrator of the Year Award. I just wanted to take this time to thank the MOSPRA organization. This is truly an honor. I would like to give recognition to the Leeton PR team who wears multiple hats within the district. Patty Cox, Kelly Fleming, Joanie Shackelford, Jessica Shaffer, Jennifer Corson, and Heather Shaffer. This is a wonderful group of ladies that jumped in with both feet when I asked them to be a part of my PR team. I am so grateful to each of you and to the members of the MOSPRA organization for their willingness to share ideas and resources that truly help rural schools.

Thank you to everyone for your kindness and warm wishes you sent congratulating me on this award.

Susan Crooks, ADMINISTRATOR OF THE YEAR - Missouri School Public Relations Association (MOSPRA)

Susan Crooks, Leeton R-X Superintendent, has been named MOSPRA's Administrator of the Year 2020 for Missouri! Susan was nominated and selected for this award based on her high quality of communication with staff, parents, and the community, her integrity, commitment, and love for the Leeton R-X School District, and her dedication to the MOSPRA organization. We are fortunate we have such an awesome leader in Mrs. Susan Crooks. Congratulations on your award!

post_text:
We will be extending our school closure through April 24th. During this time we will continue to provide educational enrichment and student meals.

Our food service department will be in the building during school closure for COVID-19 making meals for any student that has signed up to receive meals. THESE FREE MEALS ARE AVAILABLE TO ALL STUDENTS AGES 18 AND YOUNGER. If you have NOT signed up for meals and would like a "hot" lunch and breakfast for the next morning, please call the school office at 660-653-2301. You must sign up by Tuesday in order to receive meals the following Monday. These meals must be picked up between 11:00-11:30 each Monday in the back parking lot. Delivery is available to students that do not have parents at home that are capable and available to come to the school to pick up lunches. We have many volunteers helping with this project, however, in order for their safety as well, if you have the means to pick up meals, please do so. You will receive enough meals for the week. Please bring a cooler if possible.

post_text: We are excited to announce that two of our middle students, Lane Morgan and Landon Corson, are published authors! Last spring, Stephen Kozan conducted an author visit to Leeton where he spoke to students about his journey to becoming an author and the process of writing books. During his presentation, Mr. Kozan conducted a flash fiction writing opportunity where he chose Lane and Landon to become the published authors from Leeton based on their fictional writings. These students worked through the summer to write their chapters books and their finished products are finally here! Their books will be for sale at school events for purchase where you can receive an autographed copy, or you can go to the following website for purchase: http://readyaimwritekids.com/books/. All pre-sale purchases will be entered to win a Kindle Fire! A book release event will take place on February 4th during the home basketball games, where Mr. Kozan will be honoring our authors and celebrating their published books. We are so proud of Lane and Landon!

post_text:
On the 11th day before Christmas break...

Ms. Samantha Behlman has been at Leeton MS/HS for 4 years. She teaches Middle School English Language Arts and High School Speech & Debate. Mrs. Behlman loves all things Harry Potter and this is shown through her classroom decor! Ms. Behlman implements various types of project-based learning in her classroom. On a daily basis, you will see students collaborating through socratic seminars, passion projects, podcasting, and more. Ms. Behlman also sponsors middle and high school quiz bowl and shares her love of reading and writing during student book club sessions. You rock, Ms. Behlman!

Mrs. Sherry Scrivener has taught Kindergarten for the last 6 years here in Leeton. She has a background in early-childhood education, having worked in our early childhood center for many years prior. Mrs. Scrivener is passionate about all of our students and works hard to ensure our students know we care about them not just as a learner, but as a person as well. Thanks for being an amazing bucket filler, Mrs. Scrivener!

post_text:
The Leeton School District is so blessed
with talented teachers that are showcased
as we countdown to Christmas!

On the 12th day before Christmas break...

Mrs. Liane Hager has been in the Leeton School District for 3 years. She is the FCCLA sponsor and implements project-based learning with her students in culinary arts and child development through student showcases and exhibitions. Mrs. Hager and her students have even started the Bulldog Catering program this year in which they cater their delicious food for school and community events. Thank you Mrs. Hager for all you do!

Mrs. Misty Maxon has taught Art to Leeton R-X students for the last 3 years. Mrs. Maxon teaches K-12 grades. Mrs. Maxon is passionate about finding the artist in every child. She focuses on choiced based learning, which allows students to explore their artistic talents. Mrs. Maxon is also the Anime club sponsor. Thank you for being you, Mrs. Maxon! We are so fortunate to have you on #TeamLeeton!

post_text: The Leeton R-X School District is accepting applications for a temporary custodial position. This person will be responsible for helping to maintain the cleanliness of our building. Some duties include picking up trash, sweeping, vacuuming and mopping floors, cleaning and restocking bathrooms, cleaning windows and executing minor repairs and maintenance work and operating industrial cleaning equipment. We are looking for a detailed individual that likes to clean. Hours will be from 1:30 p.m. to 10:00 p.m. If you are interested, please fill out an application located on the District's website and send it to scrooks@leeton.k12.mo.us with "custodian" in the subject line or deliver it to the District office. The application deadline is Friday, December 6th.

post_text: The Principal's Student Advisory Committee headed out early this morning to travel to St. Louis to take part in the Change Starts With Me leadership workshop. This workshop focuses on learning about the effects of bullying and cyberbullying and how we, as a school, can build an action plan to help all students learn to have a voice to advocate for themselves and others in the MS/HS. #changestartswithme #kindnessmatters
